---
title: Panko Pork Cutlets with Apple Slaw Scallion Rice & Sriracha Crema
description: Pork and apple are a classic pairing for a reason—the sweet and savory flavors are so much better together. Here, we give the pork a crispy element by coating it in panko breadcrumbs, then shallow-frying until golden. The apple is tossed into a crunchy slaw with shredded cabbage, carrots, and scallion in a tangy sesame dressing. It’s all served with buttery rice and a drizzle of sriracha crema. Pro tip: We HIGHLY recommend piling some of that slaw onto the pork to create the perfect bite…
